22/09/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic left for London on Sunday (21 September) for a two-day official visit. 
He is meeting top British officials and representatives of companies interested in investing in the Bosnian Serb entity, as well as in BiH as a whole. 
His schedule includes a meeting with British Petroleum executives, expected to address opportunities in the local energy sector and cross-border oil transportation projects. 
(SRNA, BBC - 21/09/03)
